      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare the cherries and rub in the butter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 220°C fan. Line a baking tray. Tip the {{glace-cherries}} into a sieve and ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "rinse under warm water",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp99aihe0000gcv45y5z7f41"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " for ten seconds; dry on kitchen paper. Sift the {{self-raising-flour}}, {{baking-powder}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}} into a bowl. Rub in the {{unsalted-butter}} until the mixture looks like coarse breadcrumbs. Stir in the {{caster-sugar}} and the cherries.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bring together and cut",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour in the {{whole-milk}} all at once. Stir with a palette knife in figure-of-eight strokes until the dough just comes together. Tip onto a floured surface and pat to a 3 cm slab. Cut twelve rounds with a floured 5 cm cutter, pressing straight down. Re-pat the trimmings once; the second-round scones rise less so set them at the back of the tray.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 10 to 12 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Brush the tops with the beaten {{eggs}}. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes; the tops should be deep gold and the sides risen and dry. Cool on a rack for at least 5 minutes before splitting.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
